{
  "local_port": 34270,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I configure a universal remote?",
  "response": "Configuring a universal remote can vary depending on the brand and model, but here are general steps to help you set it up:\n\n1. **Identify Your Devices**: Make a note of the brand and model numbers of the devices you want to control (e.g., TV, DVD player, sound system).\n\n2. **Prepare the Remote**: Ensure your universal remote has working batteries. Remove the battery compartment cover, insert the batteries, and replace the cover.\n\n3. **Enter Programming Mode**:\n   - Most universal remotes have a \"Setup\" or \"Code Search\" button. Press and hold this button until the indicator light stays on, indicating the remote is in programming mode.\n\n4. **Enter Device Codes**:\n   - Universal remotes come with a code list booklet that matches specific codes to different devices. Find the code for your device brand and model.\n   - Use the remote's number pad to enter the code. If entered correctly, the indicator light should turn off or blink, confirming the code was accepted.\n\n5. **Auto Code Search (If Codes Don't Work)**:\n   - If you can't find the right code or if entering the code doesn't work, you can use the auto code search feature.\n   - Turn on the device you want to control.\n   - Press and hold the \"Setup\" or \"Code Search\" button until the indicator light stays on.\n   - Press the button on the remote that corresponds to the device (e.g., \"TV\", \"DVD\").\n   - Press and hold the \"Power\" button until the device turns off. The remote will cycle through codes until it finds the correct one.\n   - Once the device turns off, release the \"Power\" button and press the \"Setup\" or \"Code Search\" button to lock in the code.\n\n6. **Test the Remote**: Try using the remote to control the device. Test functions like power on/off, volume control, and channel changing to ensure everything works.\n\n7. **Repeat for Other Devices**: Follow the same steps for each device you want to control with the universal remote.\n\n8. **Save and Exit**: If your remote has a \"Save\" or \"Exit\" button, press it to exit programming mode. If not, simply wait for the indicator light to turn off.\n\n**Additional Tips**:\n- Keep the code list handy in case you need to reprogram the remote.\n- Some advanced universal remotes may require you to download an app or connect to the internet for setup.\n- If you lose the code list, many brands offer this information on their websites.\n\nIf these steps don't work, consult the user manual of your specific universal remote for detailed instructions, as different models might have slightly different procedures.",
